                                US Official News

                             July 17, 2014 Thursday

Minnesota: Statement from Governor Dayton on Mayo Clinic Earning the Ranking of
Best Hospital in the Nation for 2014-2015

LENGTH: 160  words

DATELINE: Saint Paul


Office of the Governor, The State of Minnesota has issued the following press
release:

Today, Mayo Clinic achieved the highest honor in U.S. News and World Report's
ranking of top hospitals, making it the best hospital in the country. Mayo
Clinic earned more number one rankings than any other provider, ranking  number
one or number two in 11 of the 12 specialties based on reputation, services and
volumes, safety and clinical outcomes. Following the release of the new
rankings, Governor Mark Dayton released the following statement:

"These rankings reaffirm what millions of patients and doctors around the world
already know: Mayo Clinic offers the best medical care in the world. Thanks to
the wise investment made by our State Legislature in the development of a
Destination Medical Center, I am confident Mayo will continue its tradition of
excellence into the future. Congratulations, Mayo!"

For further information please visit: http://mn.gov/governor/

